{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Considerable effort has been devoted to confirming this conjecture.",
    "Polynomial-time algorithms provably achieving non-trivial recovery above the KS threshold have been developed in [Mas14; MNS18; BLM15; AS15; Chi+25].",
    "Some hardness results below the KS threshold have been established within the Low-Degree Polynomial framework [LG24; SW25; Din+25], providing strong evidence for computational intractability in this regime.",
    "While most prior research has focused on small numbers of communities, recent attention has turned to the regime where the number of communities K grows with n. Early work by Chen and Xu [CX16] proposed polynomial-time algorithms achieving partial recovery near the KS threshold.",
    "Subsequent studies [SZ24; Chi+25] have shown that when K = o(√ n), recovery above the KS threshold is possible in polynomial time, while low-degree polynomials fail below the KS threshold, thus confirming the predictions of [Dec+11] in this regime."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "While most prior research has focused on small numbers of communities, recent attention has turned to the regime where the number of communities K grows with n. Early work by Chen and Xu [CX16] proposed polynomial-time algorithms achieving partial recovery near the KS threshold.",
    "Subsequent studies [SZ24; Chi+25] have shown that when K = o(√ n), recovery above the KS threshold is possible in polynomial time, while low-degree polynomials fail below the KS threshold, thus confirming the predictions of [Dec+11] in this regime."
  ]
}